The documentation here results in an error. 

https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/blazor/file-downloads?view=aspnetcore-6.0

```csharp
@code {
    private async Task DownloadFileFromStream()
    {
        var fileStream = GetFileStream();
        var fileName = "log.bin";

        //the using statement here causes an exception.
        using var streamRef = new DotNetStreamReference(stream: fileStream);

        await JS.InvokeVoidAsync("downloadFileFromStream", fileName, streamRef);
    }
}
````

### Expected Behavior

Code should not result in an exception. Removing the using statement seems to fix the issue but this seems like it would result in a memory leak. At best the documentation should address this. It is unclear of how to properly dispose of the stream reference without creating resource leaks.

